    ],
    "questionText": "A single-loop generator is rotating at a constant speed of 50 revolutions per second. At its maximum point of cutting flux (90 degrees), it induces a peak EMF of 325V. Based on this physical operation: 1. What is the Frequency of the resulting sine-wave? 2. What is the total Peak-to-Peak voltage? 3. Explain why the induced EMF is zero when the loop is at the 0-degree position.",
    "answerGuidance": [
      "Frequency: 50Hz (Since 1 revolution equals 1 cycle, 50 revolutions per second equals 50 cycles per second/Hertz).",
      "Peak-to-Peak Voltage: 650V (This is double the peak/amplitude value of 325V).",
      "Zero EMF Reason: At 0 degrees, the conductor is moving parallel to the magnetic flux lines, meaning it is not 'cutting' any flux, so no EMF is induced."
    ],
    "hint": "Remember that frequency is cycles per second, and peak-to-peak is the total height from the positive peak to the negative peak. For the zero-point, think about the angle of the wire relative to the flux lines."
  }
